main event: A series of unidentified objects were tracked by radar at Offutt AFB in Nebraska on multiple occasions in July 1953.
interesting points: The objects were reported as emitting blue-white light and red tracer light., They were tracked by radar with significant speed and were capable of making tight turns., The observation involved cooperation from the Ground Observer Corps and radar tracking by SCR-584., Moments of unclear visibility or weather conditions were noted during radar tracking., No photographs or physical evidence of the sightings were discovered.
witness description: members of the Ground Observer Corps and radar tracking crew
